B.T={front:0,back:1,category:2}
B.a3h=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Article 21?","Right to Life and Personal Liberty \u2014 No person shall be deprived of his life or personal liberty except according to procedure established by law.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3W=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Tropic of Cancer latitude?","23.5\xb0N \u2014 passes through 8 Indian states: Gujarat, Rajasthan, MP, Chhattisgarh, Jharkhand, WB, Tripura, Mizoram.","Geography"],t.w)
B.a3M=new A.Z(B.T,["When was GST implemented?",'July 1, 2017 \u2014 via 101st Constitutional Amendment Act, 2016. It replaced multiple indirect taxes with "One Nation, One Tax".',"Economy"],t.w)
B.a3l=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Chandrayaan-3 achievement?","India became the 4th country to land on Moon and 1st to land near the south pole. Vikram lander touched down on Aug 23, 2023.","Science"],t.w)
B.a44=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the 73rd Amendment?","Constitutionalized Panchayati Raj Institutions (1992). Added Part IX and 11th Schedule. Provides for 3-tier system at village, intermediate, and district levels.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3m=new A.Z(B.T,["What are the Fundamental Duties?","Article 51A \u2014 11 duties added by 42nd Amendment (1976) on Swaran Singh Committee recommendation. 11th duty (education of children) added by 86th Amendment.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3L=new A.Z(B.T,["What is El Ni\xf1o?","Warming of Pacific Ocean surface waters off South America. Causes drought in India, weaker monsoon. La Ni\xf1a is the opposite \u2014 cooling of Pacific, stronger monsoon.","Geography"],t.w)
B.a3R=new A.Z(B.T,["What is NITI Aayog?","National Institution for Transforming India \u2014 replaced Planning Commission on Jan 1, 2015. Acts as think tank. PM is chairman, CEO appointed by PM.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3U=new A.Z(B.T,["Who appoints the CAG?","The President of India appoints the CAG (Article 148). CAG audits all govt expenditure and reports to Parliament. Removable like a Supreme Court judge.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3C=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Western Ghats biodiversity?",'UNESCO World Heritage Site, one of 8 "hottest hotspots" of biodiversity. Home to 7,402 species of flowering plants. Runs 1,600 km from Maharashtra to Kerala.',"Environment"],t.w)
B.a3A=new A.Z(B.T,["What is SDG?","Sustainable Development Goals \u2014 17 goals adopted by UN in 2015, to be achieved by 2030. Covers poverty, hunger, health, education, climate, inequality.","International"],t.w)
B.a4d=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Money Bill (Article 110)?","Bill dealing with taxation, borrowing, Consolidated Fund. Can only be introduced in Lok Sabha. Rajya Sabha can only suggest amendments (14 days). Speaker certifies.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3D=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Agni-5?","India's ICBM with 5,000+ km range. Surface-to-surface, nuclear capable. Part of India's credible minimum deterrence strategy.","Defence"],t.w)
B.a3G=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Silk Route?","Ancient trade routes connecting China to Mediterranean (130 BC \u2013 1453 AD). Named for Chinese silk trade. Extended across Central Asia through India.","History"],t.w)
B.a3r=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Judicial Review?","Power of courts to examine constitutionality of laws. Based on Articles 13, 32, 226. Ensures rule of law and constitutional supremacy.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3S=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Repo Rate?","Rate at which RBI lends to commercial banks against government securities. Key tool for controlling inflation. Decided by MPC every 2 months.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a4i=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Article 370?","Granted special autonomous status to J&K. Abrogated on Aug 5, 2019 via Presidential Order under Article 367. J&K reorganized into two UTs.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3P=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Green Revolution?","Agricultural transformation in 1960s-70s. Led by M.S. Swaminathan. HYV seeds, chemical fertilizers, irrigation. Made India self-sufficient in food grains.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3x=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Ninth Schedule?","Added by 1st Amendment (1951). Laws in this schedule are immune from judicial review. But Coelho case (2007) holds basic structure test still applies.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3X=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Coral Bleaching?","Corals expel symbiotic algae (zooxanthellae) due to heat stress, losing color. Major threat from climate change. Affects Great Barrier Reef and Indian reefs.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a4_=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the FRBM Act?","Fiscal Responsibility and Budget Management Act, 2003. Targets fiscal deficit below 3% of GDP and eliminates revenue deficit for fiscal discipline.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3J=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Mansabdari System?","Mughal administrative system introduced by Akbar. Mansabdars held ranks (zat & sawar). Combined civil and military duties. Non-hereditary.","History"],t.w)
B.a3t=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Schedule 7 of the Constitution?","Contains 3 lists: Union List (98 subjects), State List (59 subjects), Concurrent List (52 subjects). Defines legislative powers of Centre and States.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3e=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Ozone Layer?","Layer of O\u2083 in stratosphere (15-35 km). Absorbs UV-B radiation. Depleted by CFCs. Montreal Protocol (1987) phased out ozone-depleting substances.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a4g=new A.Z(B.T,["Who is known as the Father of Indian Constitution?","Dr. B.R. Ambedkar \u2014 Chairman of the Drafting Committee. Architect of the Indian Constitution. Also championed social justice and rights of Dalits.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3I=new A.Z(B.T,["What is India's Fiscal Deficit target?","Under FRBM Act, target is below 3% of GDP. Budget 2024-25 targets 5.1% of GDP. Fiscal deficit = Total Expenditure - Total Receipts (excl. borrowings).","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3K=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Ganga Action Plan?","Launched in 1985 to clean river Ganga. Succeeded by Namami Gange (2014) with Rs 20,000 crore budget. Covers pollution abatement, rejuvenation, and conservation.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a45=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Regulating Act, 1773?","First attempt by British Parliament to control East India Company. Established Supreme Court in Calcutta. Made Governor of Bengal the Governor-General.","History"],t.w)
B.a4a=new A.Z(B.T,["What is BRICS?","Brazil, Russia, India, China, South Africa \u2014 major emerging economies. Formed in 2009. NDB (New Development Bank) established in 2015. HQ: Shanghai.","International"],t.w)
B.a3k=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Minimum Support Price (MSP)?","Government-guaranteed price for agricultural produce. Set by CACP (Commission for Agricultural Costs and Prices). Covers 23 crops. Based on A2+FL cost formula.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a49=new A.Z(B.T,["What is NavIC?","Navigation with Indian Constellation \u2014 India's regional satellite navigation system. 7 satellites: 3 in GEO + 4 in GSO. Covers India + 1,500 km. Alternative to GPS.","Science"],t.w)
B.a3u=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Right to Information Act?","RTI Act, 2005. Every citizen has right to request information from public authorities. 30-day response time. Central/State Information Commissions oversee.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3n=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Demographic Dividend?","Economic benefit from increased working-age population (15-64 years). India has ~68% working-age population. Window until 2055. Requires skill development.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3o=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Wetland Conservation?","Ramsar Convention (1971) protects wetlands. India has 80+ Ramsar sites. Wetlands provide flood control, water purification, biodiversity habitat, carbon storage.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a3p=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Non-Aligned Movement?","NAM formed during Cold War (1961). India co-founded with Yugoslavia, Egypt. Policy of not aligning with any major power bloc. Currently 120 member states.","International"],t.w)
B.a3z=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Comptroller and Auditor General?","CAG (Article 148) is the guardian of the public purse. Audits all government accounts. Appointed by President. Reports to Parliament. Cannot be removed easily.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a41=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Aditya-L1?","India's first space-based solar observatory. Placed at L1 Lagrange point (1.5M km from Earth). Carries 7 payloads. Studies solar corona, wind, and space weather.","Science"],t.w)
B.a3y=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Caste Census debate?","Last caste census was 1931. SECC 2011 collected data but not fully released. Demanded for evidence-based reservation and welfare policy targeting.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3N=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Bhakti Movement?","Medieval devotional movement (7th-17th century). Started in South India. Key saints: Ramanuja, Kabir, Guru Nanak, Mirabai, Tulsidas. United faith across castes.","History"],t.w)
B.a3Q=new A.Z(B.T,["What is a Carbon Sink?","Natural or artificial reservoir that absorbs CO\u2082. Forests, oceans, soil are natural sinks. India aims to create additional carbon sink of 2.5-3 billion tonnes by 2030.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a3B=new A.Z(B.T,["What is UAPA?","Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act \u2014 India's primary anti-terrorism law. Allows designation of organizations and individuals as terrorists. NIA investigates.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a46=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Creamy Layer?","Income threshold above which OBC members are excluded from reservation benefits. Currently \u20b98 lakh/year. Concept from Indra Sawhney case (1992).","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3V=new A.Z(B.T,["What is PLI Scheme?","Production Linked Incentive \u2014 incentives to manufacturers based on incremental sales. 14 sectors. \u20b91.97 lakh crore outlay. Boosts Make in India.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a48=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Continental Shelf?","Submerged extension of a continent up to 200 nautical miles (extendable to 350 nm). Coastal states have sovereign rights over resources. UNCLOS governs.","Geography"],t.w)
B.a4b=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Rowlatt Act?","Passed in March 1919. Allowed detention without trial. Sparked nationwide protests. Gandhi's first nationwide satyagraha. Led to Jallianwala Bagh (April 13, 1919).","History"],t.w)
B.a3q=new A.Z(B.T,["What is ENSO?","El Ni\xf1o-Southern Oscillation \u2014 coupled oceanic-atmospheric phenomenon. El Ni\xf1o = warm phase (drought in India), La Ni\xf1a = cool phase (excess rain in India).","Geography"],t.w)
B.a4f=new A.Z(B.T,["What is PM GatiShakti?","National Master Plan for multi-modal connectivity. GIS-based platform integrating 16 ministries. Reduces project delays. Infrastructure coordination and planning.","Governance"],t.w)
B.a4h=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Nuclear Triad?","Three-pronged nuclear delivery capability: land-based missiles (Agni), sea-based (Arihant class SSBN), air-based (fighter jets). India achieved full triad.","Defence"],t.w)
B.a3f=new A.Z(B.T,["What is NEP 2020?","National Education Policy 2020. 5+3+3+4 structure. Mother tongue till Class 5. Multiple entry/exit in higher education. Academic Bank of Credits. Replaced NEP 1986.","Governance"],t.w)
B.a43=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Siachen Glacier?","Longest glacier in the Karakoram at ~76 km. World's highest battlefield. India has controlled it since Operation Meghdoot (1984). Located in Ladakh.","Geography"],t.w)
B.a42=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Inter-State Council?","Constitutional body under Article 263. PM is chairman. Recommends on inter-state disputes and coordination. Constituted in 1990 on Sarkaria Commission recommendation.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3Z=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Ayushman Bharat?","Two pillars: Health & Wellness Centres (HWCs) for primary care, and PM-JAY for insurance (\u20b95 lakh/family/year). Covers 55 crore+ beneficiaries. Cashless treatment.","Governance"],t.w)
B.a3g=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Green Climate Fund?","UN fund to help developing countries combat climate change. Target: USD 100B/year (escalated to USD 300B/year at COP-29). Adaptation + mitigation projects.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a3T=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Article 356?","President's Rule \u2014 imposed when state constitutional machinery fails. Governor recommends. Max 3 years (with Parliament approval every 6 months). Bommai case set restrictions.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3H=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Eighth Schedule?","Lists 22 officially recognized languages. Started with 14 in 1950. Last additions (2003, 92nd Amendment): Bodo, Dogri, Maithili, Santhali.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3s=new A.Z(B.T,["What is QUAD?","Quadrilateral Security Dialogue \u2014 India, US, Japan, Australia. Focus: Free & Open Indo-Pacific. Not a military alliance. Vaccine, tech, climate, maritime cooperation.","International"],t.w)
B.a4j=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the CAG?","Comptroller and Auditor General (Article 148). Audits all government expenditure. Guardian of public purse. Reports to Parliament. Appointed by President.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a3O=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the National Hydrogen Mission?","Green Hydrogen Mission \u2014 \u20b919,744 crore. Target: 5 MMT/year by 2030. SIGHT program for electrolyzers. Zero-carbon fuel produced from water using renewable energy.","Science"],t.w)
B.a3d=new A.Z(B.T,["What is FATF?","Financial Action Task Force \u2014 global body combating money laundering and terror financing. Grey List = increased monitoring. Black List = sanctioned. India is a member.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3j=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Gaganyaan?","India's first human spaceflight mission. 3 crew members to LEO (400 km). TV-D1 abort test succeeded (2023). Astronauts training in Russia and India. Target: 2025.","Science"],t.w)
B.a4c=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Dandi March?","Salt March (March 12 \u2013 April 6, 1930) \u2014 Gandhi walked 388 km from Sabarmati to Dandi to make salt, defying British salt tax. Started Civil Disobedience Movement.","History"],t.w)
B.a3i=new A.Z(B.T,["What is MGNREGA?","Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act, 2005. Guarantees 100 days of wage employment per household per year. Demand-driven. Social audit mandatory.","Governance"],t.w)
B.a3v=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Biodiversity Hotspot?","Region with at least 1,500 endemic vascular plant species and 70%+ habitat loss. 36 globally, 4 in India: Western Ghats, Eastern Himalayas, Indo-Burma, Sundaland.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a4e=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Jallianwala Bagh Massacre?","April 13, 1919, Amritsar. General Dyer ordered firing on peaceful gathering. ~1,000+ killed. Hunter Commission investigated. Led to widespread anti-British sentiment.","History"],t.w)
B.a40=new A.Z(B.T,["What is BharatNet?","National fiber optic network to connect 2.5+ lakh Gram Panchayats with broadband. Backbone of Digital India. Phase 1 and 2 implemented, Phase 3 ongoing.","Science"],t.w)
B.a3F=new A.Z(B.T,["What is Carbon Credit?","One carbon credit = one tonne of CO\u2082 reduced/removed. Traded in carbon markets. India launched Carbon Credit Trading Scheme (CCTS) with BEE as administrator.","Environment"],t.w)
B.a3w=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Lokpal?","Anti-corruption ombudsman for the Centre. Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013. Chairperson + 8 members. Jurisdiction over PM (with conditions), ministers, MPs, officials.","Polity"],t.w)
B.a47=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the IMF?","International Monetary Fund \u2014 190 member countries. Provides financial stability, monetary cooperation, loans. India has 2.75% quota share. SDR is its reserve asset.","International"],t.w)
B.a3Y=new A.Z(B.T,["What is UPI?","Unified Payments Interface \u2014 real-time mobile payment system by NPCI. 12B+ transactions/month. India's digital public infrastructure success. Being adopted by other countries.","Economy"],t.w)
B.a3E=new A.Z(B.T,["What is the Arthashastra?","Ancient treatise on statecraft, economics, and military strategy by Kautilya (Chanakya). Written ~300 BCE. Covers governance, law, taxation, foreign policy, espionage.","History"],t.w)
