o=A.j0("High-probability Prelims question. Know specific instruments (ILSA, ChaSTE, RAMBHA-LP), landing coordinates, cost comparison, and why south pole matters.","",n,"","India scripted history when ISRO's Chandrayaan-3 mission successfully achieved a soft landing on the Moon's south polar region on August 23, 2023. India became the fourth country after the USA, the former Soviet Union, and China to accomplish a lunar soft landing.\n\nMission Components:\n\u2022 Vikram Lander: Named after Dr. Vikram Sarabhai, the father of Indian space program\n\u2022 Pragyan Rover: A 26 kg six-wheeled rover designed to operate for one lunar day (14 Earth days)\n\u2022 Propulsion Module: Carried the lander-rover from Earth orbit to lunar orbit\n\nKey Achievements:\n1. First mission to land near the lunar south pole (69.37\xb0S, 32.35\xb0E)\n2. Pragyan rover detected sulphur on the lunar surface for the first time in-situ\n3. ChaSTE instrument measured temperature profile of lunar topsoil\n4. ILSA recorded the first detection of a natural seismic event on the Moon\n5. RAMBHA-LP measured plasma density near the lunar surface\n\nWhy the South Pole?\nThe lunar south pole is scientifically significant because:\n- Permanently shadowed craters may contain water ice\n- Water can be used for future human habitation and as rocket fuel\n- The region has never been explored by any other mission\n\nBudget: The entire Chandrayaan-3 mission cost approximately Rs 615 crore (~$75 million), making it one of the most cost-effective lunar missions in history.","",b,A.a(["LVM3 launch from Sriharikota","Earth orbit raising maneuvers","Trans-lunar injection","Lunar orbit insertion","Propulsion module separation","Vikram lander descent","Soft landing at south pole","Pragyan rover deployment"],b8),"","a8","https://picsum.photos/seed/chandrayaan3_moon/800/400",!0,l,B.bZ,"CH-3: C=Cost Rs 615cr, H=Historic south pole landing, 3=3rd Chandrayaan; VP=Vikram+Pragyan",a0,B.ag,m,k,o,"","India becomes the fourth country to achieve a soft landing on the Moon and the first to land near the lunar south pole, marking a major milestone in space exploration.","","Chandrayaan-3: India Makes Historic Lunar South Pole Landing",a1)
