m=A.j0("High-frequency Mains topic. Focus on India's diplomatic achievements, IMEC as counter to BRI, AU inclusion for Global South, and DPI as India's soft power tool.","",l,"","India's presidency of the G20 culminated in the 18th G20 Leaders' Summit held in New Delhi on September 9-10, 2023, under the theme \"One Earth, One Family, One Future\" (Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam). The summit achieved significant breakthroughs.\n\nKey Outcomes:\n\n1. New Delhi Leaders' Declaration:\nAll 83 paragraphs were unanimously adopted \u2014 a remarkable consensus achievement given geopolitical tensions. The declaration covered climate action, digital transformation, health, gender equality, and multilateral reform.\n\n2. African Union (AU) Membership:\nThe African Union was granted permanent membership in the G20, making it the 21st member. This was one of India's key priorities, expanding representation of the Global South.\n\n3. India-Middle East-Europe Economic Corridor (IMEC):\nA landmark infrastructure project connecting India to Europe via the Middle East through rail and shipping routes. It is seen as a counterpart to China's Belt and Road Initiative.\n\n4. Global Biofuels Alliance:\nLaunched by India, the USA, and Brazil to accelerate global biofuel adoption and advance SDGs.\n\n5. Climate and SDG Commitments:\n- Tripling renewable energy capacity globally by 2030\n- Acknowledged need for $5.9 trillion for developing countries to meet NDCs by 2030\n- Green Development Pact adopted\n\n6. Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI):\nIndia showcased its DPI stack (Aadhaar, UPI, DigiLocker) and proposed a global DPI framework.","",b,A.a(["India assumes G20 presidency (Dec 2022)","200+ meetings across 60+ cities","New Delhi Leaders' Summit (Sep 9-10, 2023)","AU granted permanent membership","IMEC corridor announced","Global Biofuels Alliance launched","New Delhi Declaration adopted unanimously"],b8),"","a10","https://picsum.photos/seed/g20_india_summit/800/400",!0,j,B.bZ,"G20-INDIA: G=Global Biofuels Alliance, 20=20+1(AU), I=IMEC corridor, N=New Delhi Declaration, D=DPI showcased, I=India presidency, A=AU membership",a0,B.ag,k,i,m,"","India's G20 presidency culminates with the New Delhi Leaders' Declaration, consensus on climate finance, African Union inclusion, and a landmark connectivity corridor.","","India Hosts G20 Summit 2023: Key Outcomes and New Delhi Declaration",a3)
