l=A.j0("Important for GS-II (Governance/Schemes) and GS-I (Social issues). Track latest coverage percentages. Community participation model (VWSCs) is a key discussion point.","",k,"","The Jal Jeevan Mission (JJM), launched on August 15, 2019, has achieved a significant milestone with over 75% of rural households now having functional household tap connections (FHTCs). As of the latest data, 11.84 crore out of approximately 15.8 crore rural households have been provided with tap water supply.\n\nProgress Highlights:\n\u2022 At launch in August 2019, only 3.23 crore (17%) rural households had tap water\n\u2022 Current coverage: 11.84 crore households (75%) \u2014 an addition of 8.61 crore connections\n\u2022 Goa, Telangana, Haryana, and Punjab have achieved 100% coverage (Har Ghar Jal)\n\u2022 Over 2 lakh villages declared 'Har Ghar Jal'\n\nKey Features of the Mission:\n1. Target: Provide safe and adequate drinking water through piped supply to every rural household by 2024\n2. Budget: Rs 3.60 lakh crore with Centre:State sharing of 90:10 for NE and Himalayan states, 50:50 for others\n3. Community Participation: Village Water and Sanitation Committees (VWSCs) ensure local ownership\n4. Water Quality: 2,000+ water quality testing laboratories established; communities trained for field testing\n5. Sustainability: Focus on source sustainability, greywater management, and water conservation\n\nRelevance to UPSC:\n- SDG 6: Clean Water and Sanitation\n- Article 21: Right to clean drinking water as part of Right to Life\n- 73rd Amendment: Role of Panchayats in water supply management\n- Federal governance: Centre-State coordination model","",b,A.a(["Mission launched Aug 15, 2019","Centre-State cost sharing: 90:10 (NE) / 50:50 (others)","Village Water Committees (VWSCs) formed","Piped water connections provided","2000+ water quality labs established","States achieve 'Har Ghar Jal' status","Target: 100% coverage by 2024"],b8),"","a11","https://picsum.photos/seed/jal_jeevan/800/400",!1,i,B.bZ,"JJM: J=Jal for all, J=Jeevan (life/Art.21), M=Mission 2024 target; 75% done from 17%",a2,B.ag,j,h,l,"","India's flagship Jal Jeevan Mission crosses major milestone with 11.84 crore rural households now having functional tap water connections \u2014 targeting 100% by 2024.","","Jal Jeevan Mission: Tap Water Reaches 75% of Rural Households",a3)
