j=A.j0("Hot topic for Mains GS-II Essay. Examine both sides: efficiency vs federalism concerns. Know constitutional provisions requiring amendment and the implementation challenges.","",i,"","A high-level committee headed by former President Ram Nath Kovind has submitted its report recommending simultaneous elections (One Nation, One Election) for the Lok Sabha and all state legislative assemblies.\n\nKey Recommendations:\n1. Simultaneous elections to Lok Sabha and state assemblies in Phase 1\n2. Municipal and Panchayat elections within 100 days of general elections in Phase 2\n3. Constitutional amendments required \u2014 including amendments to Articles 83, 85, 172, 174, 356\n4. Common electoral roll and voter ID for all elections\n5. An Implementation Group to finalize the operational framework\n\nArguments in Favor:\n\u2022 Reduces election expenditure \u2014 estimated savings of Rs 4,000-5,000 crore per cycle\n\u2022 Ends policy paralysis caused by the Model Code of Conduct being in force frequently\n\u2022 Allows government to focus on governance rather than perpetual electioneering\n\u2022 Reduces burden on security forces and election machinery\n\nArguments Against:\n\u2022 May undermine the federal structure by reducing state-level political discourse\n\u2022 Voters may conflate national and local issues\n\u2022 Difficult to implement given diverse political conditions across states\n\u2022 What happens if a government loses confidence before the term \u2014 simultaneous dissolution?\n\nConstitutional Requirements:\nThe proposal requires ratification by at least 50% of state legislatures as it affects the federal structure of the Constitution.","",b,A.a(["Kovind Committee constituted","Report recommends simultaneous elections","Phase 1: Lok Sabha + state assemblies","Phase 2: Local bodies within 100 days","Constitutional amendments drafted (Art. 83, 85, 172, 174, 356)","Parliament passes amendments","Ratification by 50%+ state legislatures","Common electoral roll prepared"],b8),"","a13","https://picsum.photos/seed/one_nation_election/800/400",!1,g,B.bZ,"ONOE: O=One Nation, N=No perpetual elections, O=One exercise saves Rs 5000cr, E=Every 5 years synchronized",a0,B.ag,h,f,j,"","The government-appointed panel recommends simultaneous elections to Lok Sabha and state assemblies, proposing constitutional amendments and a common electoral roll.","","One Nation One Election: Law Commission Examines Simultaneous Polls",a3)
